=== why this is safe ===
* the next runner tick (~5 min) will reap this job normally
  (status -> completed, in-flight.json cleared)
* ~3 min after that, the detached task runs systemctl disable --now
* from that point on, no more ticks fire on this host
* this host stays SSH-reachable for ad-hoc manual use during the
  24h overlap; it just won't auto-pick anything from jobs/queue/
* tomorrow the user can simply delete the box in Hetzner Console

=== to re-enable later (if needed) ===
  systemctl enable --now jass-runner.timer

